column10:
Super fun and relaxing! It has the same charm as SR1 but is even better in terms of mechanics and UI. The graphics? Gorgeous and very very saturated (it is RAINBOW island after all).
I truly missed being able to explore new places in Slime Rancher, since I practically memorized the first game's map. It feels almost complete, too; I can't wait for the official release! I am so curious about the lore, such as [spoiler] why was the big teleport in the Glass Desert broken? who is the AI that Viktor is talking to? What caused the split in color in Starlight Stand, and the volcano eruption in Ember Valley? And lastly, are all of these questions related to the person who left Rainbow Island? [/spoiler]
Developers, please give us bee drones! I desperately need them to manage my ranch -- it takes me half an hour to catch up on ranching after going on an adventure ;-;

I got bit lost and don't know what to do in first hours lol
For sure, get your jet pack immediately!
And as much as I love to keep the Gordos alive, they must be splatted in order to progress ; ;
